Balkova Lhota is a village and municipality (obec) in Tbor District in the South Bohemian Region of the Czech Republic. The municipality covers an area of 3.53 square kilometres (1.36sqmi), and has a population of 122 (as at 2005). Balkova Lhota lies approximately 6 kilometres (4mi) north-west of Tbor, 54km (34mi) north of esk Budjovice, and 72km (45mi) south of Prague.
